ory/covid-19 COVID-19 Resource Directory on OpenMD]\n\n===Data and graphs===\n\n* [https://www.who.int/emergencies/diseases/novel-coronavirus-2019/situation-reports/ Coronavirus disease (COVID-2019) situation reports] and [https://experience.arcgis.com/experience/685d0ace521648f8a5beeeee1b9125cd map] by the World Health Organization\n* [https://www.arcgis.com/apps/opsdashboard/index.html#/bda7594740fd40299423467b48e9ecf6 Coronavirus COVID-19 Global Cases] and [https://github.com/CSSEGISandData/COVID-19 historical data] created by [[Lauren Gardner (scientist)|Lauren Gardner]] at [[Johns Hopkins University]]\n* [https://www.ecdc.europa.eu/en/publications-data/download-todays-data-geographic-distribution-covid-19-cases-worldwide Historical data about COVID-19 cases] published by the [[European Centre for Disease Prevention and Control|European Centre for Disease Prevention and Control (ECDC)]]\n* [http://unwfp.maps.arcgis.com/apps/opsdashboard/index.html#/42b8837bb25049b9b1f69a9555d55808 World Travel Restrictions] based on [[World Food Programme|WFP]] data\n* [https://covid.observer Coronavirus Observer] based on [[Johns Hopkins University]] data\n* [https://www.worldometers.info/coronavirus/ Covid-19 coronavirus pandemic] published by the [[worldometers.info|Worldometer]] website.\n* [https://ourworldindata.org/coronavirus Coronavirus Disease (COVID-19) \u2013 Statistics and Research] published by the [[Our World in Data]] website. \n* [https://covid19.healthdata.org/united-states-of-america COVID-19 Projections] for many different countries - published by [[Institute for Health Metrics and Evaluation]]. \n* [https://sites.google.com/site/pandemicdata/ Historical data with additional computations and graphs in user-friendly spreadsheet format] created by [https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/User:Dianelos Dianelos Georgoudis]\n\n===Medical journals===\n\n* [https://jamanetwork.com/journals/jama/pages/coronavirus-alert Coronavirus Disease 2019 (COVID-19)] by [[JAMA (jour