{"title_page": "Richard Hilton", "text_new": "{{Infobox person\n| birth_name  = Richard Howard Hilton\n| image       = Richard Hilton.jpg\n| image_size  = 220px\n| caption     = Hilton at daughter [[Nicky Hilton|Nicky's]] Fashion Show in March 2008\n| birth_date  = {{birth date and age|mf=yes|1955|8|17}}\n| birth_place = [[Los Angeles, California]], U.S.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://familysearch.org/ark:/61903/1:1:VG7L-4ST|title=FamilySearch: Sign In to FamilySearch|website=FamilySearch.org|access-date=January 6, 2018}}</ref>\n| parents     = [[Barron Hilton]]<br>Marilyn June Hawley\n| spouse      = {{marriage|[[Kathy Hilton]]|1979}}\n| children    = 4, including [[Paris Hilton|Paris]] and [[Nicky Hilton Rothschild|Nicky Hilton]]\n| relatives   = [[Steven M. Hilton]] {{small|(brother)}}\n| alma_mater  = [[University of Denver]] ([[Bachelor of Science|B.S.]], 1978)\n}}\n\n'''Richard Howard''' \"'''Rick'''\" '''Hilton'''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wargs.com/other/hilton.html|title=Ancestry of Paris Hilton|website=Wargs.com|access-date=January 6, 2018}}</ref> (born August 17, 1955) is an American businessman. He is the chairman and co-founder of Hilton & Hyland, a real estate brokerage firm based in [[Beverly Hills, California]], that specializes in homes and estates in Beverly Hills, [[Holmby Hills]], [[Bel-Air, California|Bel-Air]], [[Brentwood, Los Angeles|Brentwood]], [[Pacific Palisades, Los Angeles|Pacific Palisades]], [[Malibu, California|Malibu]], [[Hollywood Hills]], as well as estates from [[Santa Barbara, California|Santa Barbara]] to [[San Diego, California|San Diego]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hiltonhyland.com/associates/rick-hilton|title=Rick Hilton - Hilton & Hyland|website=HiltonHyland.com|access-date=January 6, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Biography==\n\n===Early life===\nHilton was born in Los Angeles, California, the sixth of eight children to Marilyn June (n\u00e9e Hawley) and [[Barron Hilton]], whose father was [[Hilton Hotel]] founder [[Conrad Hilton]]. In 1978, he graduated from the [[University of Denver]] with a degree in hotel and restaurant management. His brothers and sisters are: William Barron Hilton Jr. (born 1948), Hawley Anne Hilton (born 1949), [[Steven M. Hilton|Steven Michael Hilton]] (born 1950), David Alan Hilton (born 1952), Sharon Constance Hilton (born 1953), Daniel Kevin Hilton (born 1962), and Ronald Jeffrey Hilton (born 1963).\n\n===Career===\nHilton joined the New York office of Eastdil Secured,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eastdil.com/|title=Eastdil Secured|website=Eastdil.com|access-date=January 6, 2018}}</ref> a real estate investment banking firm.  He specialized in securing participation of institutional investors and pension funds in various transactions.\n\nIn 1984, he formed Hilton Realty Investment to handle commercial real estate. He obtained his broker license on November 29, 1985.<ref>[http://www2.dre.ca.gov/PublicASP/pplinfo.asp?License_id=00904327 \"Hilton, Richard Howard\" ''State of California Department of Real Estate''], July 21, 2011</ref> Hilton and [[Jeffrey Hyland]] were issued a corporation license for their real estate firm Hilton & Hyland on July 26, 1993.<ref>[http://www2.dre.ca.gov/publicasp/pplinfo.asp?License_id=01160681 \"Hilton & Hyland Real Estate Inc\" ''State of California Department of Real Estate''], July 21, 2011]</ref> Among their developments are Brentwood Country Estates.<ref>[http://www.tv.com/rick-hilton/person/285226/summary.html Rick Hilton Biography]. TV.com. Accessed 1 March 2010.</ref> Former ''[[Million Dollar Listing]]'' cast members [[Chad Rogers]] and Josh Altman; [[Frank Robinson]]'s daughter, Nichelle; [[Ron Kass]]'s son, Robert; [[Anne Heche]]'s former husband, Coleman Laffoon; Rayni Romito Williams and Branden Brent Williams<ref>[https://www.hiltonhyland.com/associates/rayni-williams/ \u201cHilton&Hyland: About Rayni Williams\u201d]</ref><ref>[https://www.hiltonhyland.com/associates/branden-williams/ \u201cHilton&Hyland: About Branded Williams\u201d]</ref>, [[Richard D. Zanuck]]'s daughter-in-law, Marisa, are among Hilton & Hyland's 106 salespeople.<ref>[http://www2.dre.ca.gov/publicasp/pplinfo.asp?function=sales&License_id=01160681&start=1 \"Salespersons Affiliated With License Number: 01160681\" ''State of California Department of Real Estate''] 21 July 2011</ref>  In 2013 Hilton & Hyland reported almost $2 billion in sales.<ref>Erin Mendell, [https://www.wsj.com/articles/SB10001424052702304250204579433361983265446 \"How Rick & Kathy Hilton Built Their Empire: Raising Paris Hilton is just part of their r\u00e9sum\u00e9. Rick and Kathy Hilton on their path to a $300 million fortune.\"] ''[[The Wall Street Journal]]'', March 28, 2014.</ref> Since 2006, Williams & Williams has been affiliated with the ''Hilton & Hyland Real Estate Inc''. Both companies joined forces to develop and distribute projects in the highly competitive real estate luxury market.<ref>{{cite news|last=Kiefer|first=Peter|title=THR's annual report on the pros making the biggest sales, including L.A.'s first-ever 10-figure listing.|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/hollywoods-top-30-real-estate-agents-1141823/item/top-30-real-estate-matt-josh-altman-1141797|accessdate=7 June 2019|newspaper=The Hollywood Reporter|date=September 14, 2018}}</ref><ref>[https://www.businessinsider.com/how-los-angeles-mega-mansions-selling-real-estate-market-strategy-2019-6 \u201cBusiness Insider,\u201d]</ref><ref>[http://labusinessjournal.com/news/2018/oct/31/whos-brokering-los-angeles-october-29-branden-and-/  \u201cLos Angeles Business Journal\u201d]</ref>\n \nHilton has also been an executive producer on several of the television series featuring his famous daughters.<ref>[https://www.questia.com/read/1G1-138413283 \"Passport to Paris\"], ''[[Daily Mail]]'', November 5, 2005 {{subscription required|via=[[Questia Online Library]]}}.</ref>\n\n===Personal life===\nHilton married [[Kathy Hilton|Kathy Avanzino]] on November 24, 1979. They have four children: [[Paris Hilton]] (born February 17, 1981), [[Nicky Hilton|Nicholai \"Nicky\" Hilton]] (born October 5, 1983), Barron Hilton II (born November 7, 1989), and Conrad Hughes Hilton III (born March 3, 1994). They live in [[Bel Air, Los Angeles]].<ref name=\"latimesstory\">Booth Moore, [http://www.latimes.com/features/image/la-ig-hilton-20121209,0,7987268.story Special occasion calls for a twist with Kathy Hilton], ''[[The Los Angeles Times]]'', December 9, 2012</ref>  Hilton has three grandchildren, a girl named Lily Grace Victoria Rothschild, who was born to their daughter Nicky and her husband James Rothschild in 2016, Teddy Marilyn Rothschild, born in 2017<ref>[http://celebritybabies.people.com/2016/07/08/nicky-hilton-rothschild-welcomes-daughter-lily-grace-victoria/ \"Nicky Hilton Rothschild Welcomes Daughter Lily Grace Victoria\"]. ''People.'' July 8, 2016. <http://people.com/babies/nicky-hilton-rothschild-welcomes-daughter-teddy-marilyn/</ref> and Milou Aliz\u00e9e Hilton, born in 2020 from his son Barron and his wife Tessa.<ref>[https://people.com/parents/barron-hilton-welcomes-daughter-milou-alizee-wife-tessa/ \"It's a Girl! Barron Hilton and Wife Tessa Welcome Daughter Milou Alizee\"]. ''People.'' March 13, 2020.</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.Instagram.com/RickHilton7 Instagram]*\n*[http://www.hilton.com Hilton International]\n*[http://www.hiltonhyland.com Hilton & Hyland]\n*{{IMDb name|1557614|Rick Hilton}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Hilton, Richard}}\n[[Category:1955 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American hoteliers]]\n[[Category:American real estate businesspeople]]\n[[Category:American socialites]]\n[[Category:Businesspeople from Los Angeles]]\n[[Category:Conrad Hilton family]]\n[[Category:People from Bel Air, Los Angeles]]\n[[Category:University of Denver alumni]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox person\n| birth_name  = Richard Howard Hilton\n| image       = Richard Hilton.jpg\n| image_size  = 220px\n| caption     = Hilton at daughter [[Nicky Hilton|Nicky's]] Fashion Show in March 2008\n| birth_date  = {{birth date and age|mf=yes|1955|8|17}}\n| birth_place = [[Los Angeles, California]], U.S.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://familysearch.org/ark:/61903/1:1:VG7L-4ST|title=FamilySearch: Sign In to FamilySearch|website=FamilySearch.org|access-date=January 6, 2018}}</ref>\n| parents     = [[Barron Hilton]]<br>Marilyn June Hawley\n| spouse      = {{marriage|[[Kathy Hilton]]|1979}}\n| children    = 4, including [[Paris Hilton|Paris]] and [[Nicky Hilton Rothschild|Nicky Hilton]]\n| relatives   = [[Steven M. Hilton]] {{small|(brother)}}\n| alma_mater  = [[University of Denver]] ([[Bachelor of Science|B.S.]], 1978)\n}}\n\n'''Richard Howard''' \"'''Rick'''\" '''Hilton'''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wargs.com/other/hilton.html|title=Ancestry of Paris Hilton|website=Wargs.com|access-date=January 6, 2018}}</ref> (born August 17, 1955) is an American businessman. He is the chairman and co-founder of Hilton & Hyland, a real estate brokerage firm based in [[Beverly Hills, California]], that specializes in homes and estates in Beverly Hills, [[Holmby Hills]], [[Bel-Air, California|Bel-Air]], [[Brentwood, Los Angeles|Brentwood]], [[Pacific Palisades, Los Angeles|Pacific Palisades]], [[Malibu, California|Malibu]], [[Hollywood Hills]], as well as estates from [[Santa Barbara, California|Santa Barbara]] to [[San Diego, California|San Diego]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hiltonhyland.com/associates/rick-hilton|title=Rick Hilton - Hilton & Hyland|website=HiltonHyland.com|access-date=January 6, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Biography==\n\n===Early life===\nHilton was born in Los Angeles, California, the sixth of eight children to Marilyn June (n\u00e9e Hawley) and [[Barron Hilton]], whose father was [[Hilton Hotel]] founder [[Conrad Hilton]]. In 1978, he graduated from the [[University of Denver]] with a degree in hotel and restaurant management. His brothers and sisters are: William Barron Hilton Jr. (born 1948), Hawley Anne Hilton (born 1949), [[Steven M. Hilton|Steven Michael Hilton]] (born 1950), David Alan Hilton (born 1952), Sharon Constance Hilton (born 1953), Daniel Kevin Hilton (born 1962), and Ronald Jeffrey Hilton (born 1963).\n\n===Career===\nHilton joined the New York office of Eastdil Secured,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eastdil.com/|title=Eastdil Secured|website=Eastdil.com|access-date=January 6, 2018}}</ref> a real estate investment banking firm.  He specialized in securing participation of institutional investors and pension funds in various transactions.\n\nIn 1984, he formed Hilton Realty Investment to handle commercial real estate. He obtained his broker license on November 29, 1985.<ref>[http://www2.dre.ca.gov/PublicASP/pplinfo.asp?License_id=00904327 \"Hilton, Richard Howard\" ''State of California Department of Real Estate''], July 21, 2011</ref> Hilton and [[Jeffrey Hyland]] were issued a corporation license for their real estate firm Hilton & Hyland on July 26, 1993.<ref>[http://www2.dre.ca.gov/publicasp/pplinfo.asp?License_id=01160681 \"Hilton & Hyland Real Estate Inc\" ''State of California Department of Real Estate''], July 21, 2011]</ref> Among their developments are Brentwood Country Estates.<ref>[http://www.tv.com/rick-hilton/person/285226/summary.html Rick Hilton Biography]. TV.com. Accessed 1 March 2010.</ref> Former ''[[Million Dollar Listing]]'' cast members [[Chad Rogers]] and Josh Altman; [[Frank Robinson]]'s daughter, Nichelle; [[Ron Kass]]'s son, Robert; [[Anne Heche]]'s former husband, Coleman Laffoon; Rayni Romito Williams and Branden Brent Williams<ref>[https://www.hiltonhyland.com/associates/rayni-williams/ \u201cHilton&Hyland: About Rayni Williams\u201d]</ref><ref>[https://www.hiltonhyland.com/associates/branden-williams/ \u201cHilton&Hyland: About Branded Williams\u201d]</ref>, [[Richard D. Zanuck]]'s daughter-in-law, Marisa, are among Hilton & Hyland's 106 salespeople.<ref>[http://www2.dre.ca.gov/publicasp/pplinfo.asp?function=sales&License_id=01160681&start=1 \"Salespersons Affiliated With License Number: 01160681\" ''State of California Department of Real Estate''] 21 July 2011</ref>  In 2013 Hilton & Hyland reported almost $2 billion in sales.<ref>Erin Mendell, [https://www.wsj.com/articles/SB10001424052702304250204579433361983265446 \"How Rick & Kathy Hilton Built Their Empire: Raising Paris Hilton is just part of their r\u00e9sum\u00e9. Rick and Kathy Hilton on their path to a $300 million fortune.\"] ''[[The Wall Street Journal]]'', March 28, 2014.</ref> Since 2006, Williams & Williams has been affiliated with the ''Hilton & Hyland Real Estate Inc''. Both companies joined forces to develop and distribute projects in the highly competitive real estate luxury market.<ref>{{cite news|last=Kiefer|first=Peter|title=THR's annual report on the pros making the biggest sales, including L.A.'s first-ever 10-figure listing.|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/hollywoods-top-30-real-estate-agents-1141823/item/top-30-real-estate-matt-josh-altman-1141797|accessdate=7 June 2019|newspaper=The Hollywood Reporter|date=September 14, 2018}}</ref><ref>[https://www.businessinsider.com/how-los-angeles-mega-mansions-selling-real-estate-market-strategy-2019-6 \u201cBusiness Insider,\u201d]</ref><ref>[http://labusinessjournal.com/news/2018/oct/31/whos-brokering-los-angeles-october-29-branden-and-/  \u201cLos Angeles Business Journal\u201d]</ref>\n \nHilton has also been an executive producer on several of the television series featuring his famous daughters.<ref>[https://www.questia.com/read/1G1-138413283 \"Passport to Paris\"], ''[[Daily Mail]]'', November 5, 2005 {{subscription required|via=[[Questia Online Library]]}}.</ref>\n\n===Personal life===\nHilton married [[Kathy Hilton|Kathy Avanzino]] on November 24, 1979. They have four children: [[Paris Hilton]] (born February 17, 1981), [[Nicky Hilton|Nicholai \"Nicky\" Hilton]] (born October 5, 1983), Barron Hilton II (born November 7, 1989), and Conrad Hughes Hilton III (born March 3, 1994). They live in [[Bel Air, Los Angeles]].<ref name=\"latimesstory\">Booth Moore, [http://www.latimes.com/features/image/la-ig-hilton-20121209,0,7987268.story Special occasion calls for a twist with Kathy Hilton], ''[[The Los Angeles Times]]'', December 9, 2012</ref>  Hilton has three grandchildren, a girl named Lily Grace Victoria Rothschild, who was born to their daughter Nicky and her husband James Rothschild in 2016, Teddy Marilyn Rothschild, born in 2017<ref>[http://celebritybabies.people.com/2016/07/08/nicky-hilton-rothschild-welcomes-daughter-lily-grace-victoria/ \"Nicky Hilton Rothschild Welcomes Daughter Lily Grace Victoria\"]. ''People.'' July 8, 2016. <http://people.com/babies/nicky-hilton-rothschild-welcomes-daughter-teddy-marilyn/</ref> as well as a third granddaughter born in 2020 named Milou Aliz\u00e9e Hilton from his son Barron and his wife Tessa.<ref>[https://people.com/parents/barron-hilton-welcomes-daughter-milou-alizee-wife-tessa/ \"It's a Girl! Barron Hilton and Wife Tessa Welcome Daughter Milou Alizee\"]. ''People.'' March 13, 2020.</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.Instagram.com/RickHilton7 Instagram]*\n*[http://www.hilton.com Hilton International]\n*[http://www.hiltonhyland.com Hilton & Hyland]\n*{{IMDb name|1557614|Rick Hilton}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Hilton, Richard}}\n[[Category:1955 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American hoteliers]]\n[[Category:American real estate businesspeople]]\n[[Category:American socialites]]\n[[Category:Businesspeople from Los Angeles]]\n[[Category:Conrad Hilton family]]\n[[Category:People from Bel Air, Los Angeles]]\n[[Category:University of Denver alumni]]\n", "name_user": "Mgasparin", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200ePersonal life", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Richard_Hilton"}
{"title_page": "Lords and Ladies (novel)", "text_new": "{{Infobox book\n| name         = Lords and Ladies\n| image        = lords-and-ladies-cover.jpg\n| caption      = Hardcover edition\n| author       = [[Terry Pratchett]]\n| illustrator  = \n| cover_artist = \n| language     = English\n| series       = ''[[Discworld]]''<br />14th novel \u2013 4th witches story\n| subject      = [[William Shakespeare|Shakespeare]], [[Crop circle]]s, [[Fairy]] lore\n| genre        = [[Fantasy]]\n| publisher    = [[Victor Gollancz]]\n| pub_date     = 1992\n| pages        = \n| awards       = \n| isbn         = 0-575-05223-6\n}}\n'''''Lords and Ladies''''' is a [[fantasy novel]] by British writer [[Terry Pratchett]], the fourteenth ''[[Discworld]]'' book. It was originally published in 1992.<ref>Fantastic Fiction [http://www.fantasticfiction.co.uk/p/terry-pratchett/lords-and-ladies.htm Lords and Ladies (Discworld, book 14) Terry Pratchett] Retrieved 2009-05-9</ref>  Some parts of the storyline spoof elements of [[William Shakespeare|Shakespeare's]] play ''[[A Midsummer Night's Dream]]''.\n\n==Synopsis==\n[[Granny Weatherwax]], [[Nanny Ogg]], and [[Magrat Garlick]]  return to [[Lancre]] after their [[Witches Abroad|recent adventure]] in [[Genua (Discworld)|Genua]]. Magrat is stunned when [[Verence II|King Verence]] proclaims their imminent marriage, having already made all the arrangements in her absence.  The sudden appearance of [[crop circles]] reveals to Nanny and Granny that it is now \"circle time\", a convergence of [[Multiverse|parallel universes]] when the Discworld is susceptible to incursions from the \"parasite universe\" of the Elves. Elves are capricious and amoral creatures that enter the minds of animals and sentient beings in a more destructive way than witches do, using \"glamour\" to alter human's perceptions of them.  They are normally kept away by a circle of [[Magnetism|magnetized]] iron [[standing stones]] known as the Dancers. When Nanny and Granny refuse to explain the situation to Magrat, she leaves the coven, disavows witchcraft, and moves into an apartment in Lancre Castle.  She soon becomes bored with the courtly lifestyle and unsure of her place.\n\n[[Mustrum Ridcully]], Archchancellor of [[Unseen University]], leads a small group of faculty to attend the wedding.  Along the way, they are joined by the Dwarfish lothario [[Casanunda]].\n\nGranny and Nanny discover that a group of local girls, led by [[Witches (Discworld)#Diamanda Tockley|Diamanda Tockley]] and including  [[Agnes Nitt]], have formed a new coven whose activities include dancing naked at the Dancers.  The two elderly witches try to convince them to stop, with Granny ultimately besting Diamanda in a public witchcraft contest and discrediting the new coven.  But a defiant Diamanda later runs through the Dancers into the land of the Elves, where she is knocked unconscious by a poisoned Elven arrow before being rescued by Granny.  Nanny subdues an Elf that pursues them back into Lancre, using an iron fireplace poker; Elves and their powers are severely weakened by iron.  The witches bring Diamanda and the Elf to Lancre Castle, where Magrat treats Diamanda and Verence agrees to imprison the Elf (though Magrat inadvertently frees it later).  Meanwhile, Granny has begun to experience memories of other paths her life has taken in parallel worlds, as well as a growing sense of her own impending death.\n\n[[Jason Ogg]] and the other Lancre Morris Men plan a play to be performed for the wedding guests.  When they rehearse near the Dancers, the Elves influence them to include Elvish elements in the play.  As a result, when the play is performed at the Dancers, it causes sufficient belief\u2014a powerful force on the Discworld\u2014that the Elves are able to make the guests dismantle the stone circle. The Elves arrive, and the Elf Queen plans to legitimize her rule of Lancre by marrying Verence.  None of the members of the Lancre coven are present at this time: Magrat has locked herself in her room due to perceived insults in a letter she has discovered, written by Granny to Verence, advising him to plan the wedding; Nanny is being romanced by Casanunda; and Granny has been magically whisked away by Ridcully, who hopes to resume a romantic connection they had when much younger.  The women only become aware of what has happened once the Elves begin to wreak havoc in Lancre.  Aided only by general [[Dogsbody|dogsbody]] [[Shawn Ogg]], Magrat fights her way through the infiltrated castle.  She discovers a portrait of Queen Ynci, one of the kingdom's legendary founders.  Suddenly inspired by the idea of becoming a ''warrior ''queen, Magrat finds and dons Ynci's [[armour]].  Feeling influenced by Ynci's spirit (and unaware that Ynci is a fiction, the armour constructed from cookware only a few generations previously), she rescues a captured Shawn and sets out for the Dancers.  While Granny and Ridcully make their way through the woods, resulting in Granny's capture by the Elves, Nanny and Casanunda travel through a gateway to the abode of the Elf King, who opposes the Elf Queen despite being her spouse.\n\nAt the Dancers, Magrat arrives to confront the Elf Queen at the same time as the people of Lancre, rallied by Shawn and Nanny.  But the Elf Queen quickly subdues Magrat with glamour.  The captive Granny mentally combats the Elf Queen and releases Magrat from the glamour before succumbing to the Elf Queen's attack, her prone body being covered by the bees from her hive, which have swarmed at the Dancers.  When the Elf Queen turns her powers on Magrat, attempting to stop her resistance by dismantling her identity, she exposes the unexpectedly valorous core of Magrat's being, (something which Granny had deliberately been stoking, aggravating and provoking all along for just this very outcome).  Magrat attacks and subdues the Elf Queen just in time for a projection of the Elf King to arrive and send the Elves back to their world.\n\nGranny appears to be dead, but then Nanny and Magrat learn that she has actually borrowed her bees' hive mind; a feat thought impossible.  They break open a window in the castle, where Ridcully has reverently laid Granny's body, enabling the bees to get close enough for her to regain consciousness.  Nanny points out to Magrat that Granny's letter to Verence has had a great positive impact on Magrat's life, as well as giving her the strength to fight the Elf Queen.  Magrat and Verence are married by Ridcully.  Later, Granny and Ridcully make peace with their past and their place in the universe.  The growing sense of impending death she had been feeling had been due to the impending deaths of some of her parallel-selves.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{wikiquote|Discworld#Lords and Ladies|Lords and Ladies}}\n* {{isfdb title|272}}\n*[http://www.lspace.org/books/apf/lords-and-ladies.html Annotations at the L-Space Web]\n*[http://www.lspace.org/books/pqf/lords-and-ladies.html Quotations]\n* [http://www.lspace.org/books/synopses/lords-and-ladies.html Synopsis]\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-other|[[Discworld reading order|Reading order guide]]}}\n{{succession box | before = [[Small Gods]]| title = 14th [[Discworld#Novels|Discworld Novel]]  | years= | after = [[Men at Arms]]}}\n{{succession box | before = [[Witches Abroad]]| title = 4th [[Witches (Discworld)|Witches Story]]  | years=Published in 1992  | after = [[Maskerade]]}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{Discworld books}}\n{{Terry Pratchett}}\n{{A Midsummer Night's Dream}}\n\n[[Category:1992 British novels]]\n[[Category:Discworld books]]\n[[Category:1992 fantasy novels]]\n[[Category:Novels about parallel universes]]\n[[Category:Elves in popular culture]]\n[[Category:Works based on A Midsummer Night's Dream]]\n[[Category:Novels based on plays]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox book\n| name         = Lords and Ladies\n| image        = lords-and-ladies-cover.jpg\n| caption      = Hardcover edition\n| author       = [[Terry Pratche